rting of results. Duties ( Not all inclusive) Work with and supervise others in data collection, data cleaning and processing, and big data applications. Maintain relevant databases and time series up to date in order to facilitate responses to requests in a timely manner. Apply knowledge of probability theory and statistics to determine sample size for desired confidence interval, design representative and convenience surveys (random, stratified, cluster), test survey instruments, administer and supervise surveys (in-person, telephone, online), clean and analyze data, Support the development forecasts of economic and market trends, in particular government tax revenues and tax effort, under different scenarios assuring that the statistical techniques are the most appropriate and reliable given constraints. Communicate to both internal and external clients in clear, coherent, and dynamic manner in both written and oral form. Prepare short written reports and presentations for the Chief Economic and the Director of the Office of Management. Build and use data visualizations and communicate with technical and non-technical audiences to include senior government officials, legislators, business leaders, academic leaders, and the media outlets. Use tableau and similar programs to make website and presentations more dynamic and interactive. Code and develop applets that will allow the department to use mobile platforms for the execution of surveys, polls, and faster gathering of information. Be able if necessary to write programs to manipulate data in databases. Cultivate, develop, and maintain contacts with other important centers/entities for data collection in the territory. Maintain and build good relationships with staff of federal agencies to include the Department of Commerce\u2019s-Economic Development Administration, Bureau of Economic Analysis, Department of the Interior. Supervise and manage external consultants working on behalf of the Department. Mentor, guide, and develop junior staff. Assist with the elaboration, revision, and dissemination of the Comprehensive Economic Development Strategy Plan, Tourism Master Plan, and other flagship initiatives. Conduct special topical research papers and produce periodic economic situation and outlook reports under the guidance of the Chief Economist. Assist in completing, reviewing, and finalizing publications of the division. Assist in the development of grant proposals. Represent the Chief Economist at meetings and/or conferences when called upon. Perform other duties and activities as required. Competencies and Work Conditions Factor 1- Knowledge and Skills Required for the Position Â· Strategic Vision: Fair level understanding of global, national, regional, and local economic trends, opportunities, and challenges. Â· Leadership: Demonstrated intellectual leadership topics of statistics, probability theory, data science, and computer programming. Â· Analytical Capacity: Ability to undertake rigorous and thorough analysis of economic and social data. Â· Quantitative Skills: Knowledge of statistics. , data science, computer programming, database programs. Experience in working with large datasets, and using statistics and quantitative methods to analyze data. Â· Communication: Strong verbal and written communication skills with ability to convey complex matters clearly and succinctly to non-technical audiences. Â· Interpersonal Skills: Able to work in a team environment and establish good working relationships with co-workers, supervisors, and persons outside of the departments in other relevant entities. Able to work with others in a fair and respectful manner and inspire high performance from teammates. Factor 2 -Supervisory Controls Â· Incumbent must have experience working in a team environment, work well under pressure, and meet deadlines. Some experience with project and people management is desirable. Supervision may be exercised over subordinate Division of Economic Res