anguages as well as Excel, Word, and PowerPoint. Certification in data science would be highly desirable. OR Bachelor\u2019s degree in Statistics or related quantitative methods field from an accredited college or university. Seven years professional experience in economic research. Two years\u2019 additional experience in a policy related position engaged in economic and social analysis is a plus. Should be proficient in use of leading statistical software programs as well as Excel, Word, and PowerPoint. Certification in data science would highly desirable. OR Ten years minimum professional experience in applied statistical analysis and database creation and maintenance. Should be proficient in use of leading statistical software programs as well as Excel, Word, and PowerPoint. Certification in data science would highly desirable. Job Type: Full-time Salary: $55,000.00 to $70,000.00 /year Benefits: 401(k) Dental Insurance Disability Insurance Employee Assistance Program Health Insurance Life Insurance Paid Time Off Retirement Plan Vision Insurance Schedule: Monday to Friday COVID-19 considerations: To keep our employees safe we provided a reusable mask, disinfectant wipes throughout the office, an industrial sanitizing of the office and are currently upgrading our cleaning methods for daily preservation of individual well-being. Experience: Data Science: 5 years (Preferred) Economic Research: 5 years (Required) Education: Bachelor's (Preferred) Location: St Thomas, VI 00802 (Required) Language: English (Required) Work authorization: United States (Required) Work Location: One location Company's website: https://omb.vi.gov/ Benefit Conditions: Waiting period may apply Only full-time employees eligible Work Remotely: No Show full job description Quick Apply Stay Connected Contact Us SimplyHired Blog Facebook Twitter LinkedIn YouTube Job Tools Local Jobs Salary Estimator Post Jobs Free Resume Builder Browse All Jobs All Salaries All Cities All Companies Guides Resumes